ps — list running processes

SYNOPSIS
  ps

DESCRIPTION
  Prints every entry in the kernel process table: pid, status
  (ready / running / sleeping / waiting / paused / dead), name, and
  the command line the process was invoked with.

  OCOS uses cooperative scheduling — there are no kernel threads —
  so "running" only ever applies to the single process the scheduler
  is currently servicing.

SEE ALSO
  kill(1), svc(1), inspect(1)
